					<div class="commentheading">On February 05, 2007 at 04:17 AM, an anonymous reader said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Re: More about wild vs fresh</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Anonymous wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'> I read an article not long ago where a reporter in New York bought supposedly "wild" salmon from a number of reputable fish dealers, yet when they were tested for dye (farmed fish are actually dyed orange - yech!) nearly all of them were positive for the dye.  <br />
</div></div><br />
<br />
Farmed salmon are given the carotenoids canthaxanthin and astaxanthin along with their feed.  Wild salmon naturally get these same pigments from their diet (e.g. shellfish).  So I would assume all salmon, wild or not, would test positive for this "dye".</div>
