1. Many have complained about the degree of saltiness in their preparations, and the perceived wisdom appears to be - less salt, or less cure time. It occurs to me that the stroger concentration of salt will be located at the point of entry, namely the skinned side of the filet. However, if we skin the entire filet and apply the rub evenly to both sides, aren't we likely to get a more even distribution throughout the filet, whereby we can control the degree of saltinedd by cure time alone?<br />
